(firstQuint)Global Behavior and Periodontal Disease in Down's Syndrome Patients.

 There is a higher prevalence and severity of periodontal disease in Down's Syndrome patients.

 Plaque levels in these patients are high due to poor hygiene habits.

 Behavior also may contribute to the overall periodontal condition.

